The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Sunday, December 14, 2003 				 Pavarotti weds former secretary
				 	 Luciano Pavarotti kisses Nicoletta Mantovani after their wedding in Modena, Italy. (AFP) Modena (Italy), Dec. 13  (Reuters): Opera star Luciano Pavarotti married his ex-secretary  Nicoletta Mantovani today at a ceremony in northern Italy  boasting an array of celebrities and hosted by the couples  baby daughter.																								The pair, who tied the knot in the singers home town of Modena, have been together since the mid-1990s when Pavarotti left his first wife for Mantovani, who is half his age.																								Alice joyfully invites you to the wedding of daddy Luciano and mummy Nicoletta, read the invitation from the couples 11-month-old daughter.																								A host of stars, including Irish rocker Bono and Italian singer Zucchero, turned out for the wedding. Crowds of local residents watched the bride arrive in a limousine decorated with pink flowers. Pink too were the Giorgio Armani dresses worn by the bride and her daughter. 
